Ingredients.1: 1 pound russet potatoes, peeled and grated

Ingredients.5: 1 salt and ground black pepper to taste

Directions.1: Preheat an air fryer to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).

Directions.2: Place potatoes on a clean kitchen towel and squeeze out any excess moisture. Transfer to a bowl and stir in eggs, onion, bread crumbs, salt, and pepper.

Directions.3: Spray the air fryer basket with nonstick spray. Drop 1/4 cupfuls potato mixture into the basket. Spray tops with nonstick spray.

Directions.4: Air fry until crispy and golden brown, 8 to 12 minutes.
